{{if {{.g == 1}} }}{{setvar::active_direction::I want the ELEGANCE. Swords that move like water. Qi flowing through the body like breath. Fighters who leap into bamboo canopies and trade blows while the leaves fall around them and every movement is poetry. The martial art isn't violence here, it's philosophy made physical. The fight should feel like a dance where both people know the steps and the beauty IS the danger. Flowing robes, impossible grace, and underneath it all the discipline of a fighter who trained for decades to make this look effortless.
